item.description:
The main purpose of JOIN table engine is to avoid building the right table for joining on each query execution. So it&rsquo;s usually used when you have a high amount of fast queries which share the same right table for joining.
Updates It&rsquo;s possible to update rows with setting join_any_take_last_row enabled.
CREATETABLEid_val_join(`id`UInt32,`val`UInt8)ENGINE=Join(ANY,LEFT,id)SETTINGSjoin_any_take_last_row=1Ok.INSERTINTOid_val_joinVALUES(1,21)(1,22)(3,23);Ok.SELECT*FROM(SELECTtoUInt32(number)ASidFROMnumbers(4))ASnANYLEFTJOINid_val_joinUSING(id)┌─id─┬─val─┐│0│0││1│22││2│0││3│23│└────┴─────┘INSERTINTOid_val_joinVALUES(1,40)(2,24);Ok.SELECT*FROM(SELECTtoUInt32(number)ASidFROMnumbers(4))ASnANYLEFTJOINid_val_joinUSING(id)┌─id─┬─val─┐│0│0││1│40││2│24││3│23│└────┴─────┘{% embed url=&ldquo;https://clickhouse.tech/docs/en/engines/table-engines/special/join/&quot; %}
